.:: Puzzle 2x7-Level-6-5::.
There 7 different types of food: pomegranate, corn, lemon, potato, apricot, peas, kale
The people use 7 different means of transport: bus, ship, quad-bike, tram, trike, car, bike
 1. the person driving the trike is on the right of the person eating potato##1
 2. the person eating peas is somewhere to the left of the person eating corn##5
 3. the person driving the tram is somewhere to the left of the person driving the ship##5
 4. the person eating pomegranate is on the right of the person eating kale##1
 5. the person eating peas is somewhere to the left of the person eating potato##5
 6. the person driving the tram is somewhere to the right of the person eating apricot##5
 7. the person eating apricot is on the left of the person eating peas##1
 8. the person driving the trike is on the right of the person driving the quad-bike##1
 9. the person driving the ship is on the left of the person eating pomegranate##1
10. the person driving the ship is in the middle##1
11. the person eating lemon is on the far right##1
12. the person driving the car is on the left of the person driving the quad-bike##1
13. the person driving the bus is not the person eating corn##6
14. the person driving the quad-bike is somewhere to the right of the person driving the bike##5
15. the person eating potato is on the right of the person driving the car##1
16. the person driving the bike is on the far left or far right##3
17. the person eating kale is somewhere to the right of the person eating apricot##5
18. the person eating peas is not the person driving the quad-bike##6
19. the person eating peas is between the person eating apricot and the person driving the tram##2
20. the person eating kale is on the left of the person eating pomegranate##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1     |    2     |      3      |    4    |   5    |     6     |     7      |
